# Mosaic local configuration — copy to `.env` (gitignored) and fill in.
# `.env` is read by docker-compose for ${...} interpolation and by local runs.
#
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# COST MODEL — read before setting a key.
#
# A real OpenAI call fires ONLY when BOTH are true for an agent:
#   1. MOSAIC_<agent>_PROVIDER=live   AND   2. OPENAI_API_KEY is set
# Missing either → that agent demotes to fixture ($0). See cmd/mosaicdemo/models.go.
#
# MOSAIC_SIM_MODE adds a second dimension:
#   fixture | passthrough | (empty) → deterministic fixtures        · no key · $0
#   replay                          → plays back BANKED real output  · no key · $0
#   live | record                   → real calls (if provider+key)   · key    · $$$
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Secrets (never commit real values; this file ships placeholders only).
OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-REPLACE_ME
FAL_KEY=REPLACE_ME

# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# SAFE for demos / prep — $0, no credits spent even with a key present.
# Belt-and-suspenders: providers=fixture guarantees no calls regardless of key.
# Uncomment this block for demo prep.
# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
MOSAIC_SIM_MODE=fixture
MOSAIC_LUNA_PROVIDER=fixture
MOSAIC_TERRA_PROVIDER=fixture
MOSAIC_SOL_PROVIDER=fixture

# To demo REAL model output at $0: first do ONE record pass (see SPENDS block),
# then flip to replay — plays banked Luna/Terra/Sol cassette responses, no key,
# offline-safe (MOSAIC_CASSETTE_DIR defaults under the process temp dir, or set
# it to a local gitignored recordings/ path):
#   MOSAIC_SIM_MODE=replay
#   MOSAIC_CASSETTE_DIR=recordings

# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# SPENDS money — real OpenAI calls on interactive /operator/* routes only
# (Play beats stay fixture). Use deliberately, e.g. a one-time record pass to
# bank Luna/Terra/Sol cassette files, then switch back to replay above.
# Requires a funded OPENAI_API_KEY.
# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# MOSAIC_SIM_MODE=record
# MOSAIC_CASSETTE_DIR=recordings
# MOSAIC_LUNA_PROVIDER=live
# MOSAIC_TERRA_PROVIDER=live
# MOSAIC_SOL_PROVIDER=live

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Store selection (see docs/runbook/cloud-run-deployment-analysis.md §0).
# Unset → local Postgres container. Set a Supabase DSN to share ONE database
# with the Cloud Run demo. Prefer the session pooler (IPv4, port 5432):
#   MOSAIC_DB_PATH=postgres://postgres.<ref>:PW@aws-0-<region>.pooler.supabase.com:5432/postgres?sslmode=require
# Direct db.<ref>.supabase.co is often IPv6-only on free tier and fails from
# Docker/desktop IPv4 networks. Do NOT use transaction pooler port 6543
# (breaks pgx prepared statements + migration DDL).

# MOSAIC_PORT=8080
